HEADWORD: cachalot
<hw>cach"a*lot</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>cachalot</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Zo⟦oum⟧l.)</fld> <def>The sperm whale
(<spn>Physeter macrocephalus</spn>). It has in the top of its head a
large cavity, containing an oily fluid, which, after death, concretes
into a whitish crystalline substance called <prod>spermaceti</prod>. See
<er>Sperm whale</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

